中国科研团队发现“新冠病毒已突变”。
The Chinese team found that the "new crown virus has mutated."
澎湃新闻                      。
The news is roaring.
澎湃新闻。
The news is roaring.
有内涵的时政新媒体。
Connotation of the new political media.
澎湃新闻记者 张若婷 贺梨萍新冠病毒是否已经发生突变？如何突变？这是目前学界研究的焦点之一。
Is there a mutation in Peng Li Ping's new crown virus? How to mutate? This is one of the focus of the current academic research.
中国科研团队最新发现显示：新冠病毒已于近期产生了149个突变点，并演化出了两个亚型，分别是L亚型和S亚型。
The new crown virus has recently produced 149 mutation sites and evolved into two subtypes, L subtype and S subtype, according to a new discovery by Chinese researchers.
研究发现，在地域分布及人群中的比例，这两个亚型表现出了很大差异。
The study found significant differences between the two subtypes in terms of geographical distribution and proportion of population.
其中S型是相对更古老的版本，而L亚型更具侵略性传染力更强。
The S-type is a relatively older version, while the L subtype is more aggressive and contagious.
对不同亚型的深入了解，将有助于新冠肺炎的差异化的治疗和防控。
In-depth understanding of different subtypes will be helpful to the differential treatment and prevention of new crown pneumonia.
以上研究来自中国科学院主办的《国家科学评论》（National Science Review）于3月3日发表的论文《关于SARS-CoV-2的起源和持续进化》（On the origin and continuing evolution of SARS-CoV-2）。
The study comes from the March 3 paper "On the Origin and Continuing Evolution of SARS-CoV-2," published by the National Science Review of the Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS-CoV-2).
论文通讯作者为陆剑研究员（北京大学生命科学学院生物信息中心）、崔杰研究员（中国科学院上海巴斯德研究所）。
The authors of the thesis are Lu Jian Researcher (Bioinformatics Center of Beijing University School of Life Sciences) and Cui Jie Researcher (Shanghai Pasteur Institute of Chinese Academy of Sciences).
论文通过对目前为止最大规模的103个新冠病毒全基因组分子进化分析，发现病毒株已发生了149个突变点，而且多数是近期产生的。
Based on an analysis of the genome-wide molecular evolution of the largest 103 new crown viruses to date, 149 mutation sites have been identified, most of them recently.
该研究揭示：新冠病毒已经演化出L和S两个亚型。
The study revealed that the new crown virus has evolved into two subtypes, L and S.
其中101个属于这两个亚型。
Of these, 101 belonged to these two subtypes.
从占比上看，L亚型更为普遍达到70%，S亚型占30%。
In terms of percentage, L subtypes are more common at 70 per cent and S subtypes at 30 per cent.
论文作者认为，根据新型冠状病毒的演变方式推测，L亚型和S亚型的传播能力、致病严重程度或许存在较大区别。
According to the evolution of the new coronavirus, the transmission ability and severity of L-subtype and S-subtype may be different.
论文称，两个亚型的区别在于病毒RNA基因组的第28144位点，L亚型是T碱基（对应亮氨酸，Leu），S亚型是C碱基（对应丝氨酸，Ser）。
The difference between the two subtypes is the 28144 locus of the viral RNA genome, the L subtype being the T base (corresponding to leucine, Leu) and the S subtype being the C base (corresponding to serine, Ser).
通过与其他冠状病毒比较，作者发现S型新冠病毒与蝙蝠来源的冠状病毒在进化树上更接近，从而得出S型相对更古老的结论。
Comparing with other coronavirus, the authors found that the coronavirus from the bat was closer to the coronavirus from bat source, which leads to the conclusion that the S-shape is older.
L亚型在武汉暴发的早期阶段更为普遍，而L亚型的发生频率在2020年1月初后有所下降。
L subtypes were more common in the early stages of the Wuhan outbreak, while the frequency of L subtypes decreased after the beginning of January 2020.
作者认为，人为干预可能对L亚型施加了更大的选择性压力，如果没有这些干预，L亚型可能更具侵略性和扩散得更快速。
In the authors' view, human intervention may have exerted more selective pressure on the L subtype, without which the L subtype might have been more aggressive and spread faster.
另一方面，由于选择压力相对较弱，在进化上较老且攻击性较小的S型可能在相对频率上有所增加。
On the other hand, the older and less aggressive S-type may have increased in relative frequency due to relatively weak selection pressures.
这些发现意味着，目前迫切需要结合基因组数据、流行病学数据和2019年冠状病毒病患者临床症状图表记录，进行进一步的全面研究。
These findings suggest that there is an urgent need for further comprehensive research combining genomic data, epidemiological data and a tabular record of clinical symptoms of patients with coronavirus 2019.
另外，值得注意的是，这103个样本显示，大部分患者只感染了L亚型或S亚型中的一个。
In addition, it is worth noting that the majority of these 103 samples showed that the majority of patients were infected with only one of the L subtypes or S subtypes.
但其中一位近期有过武汉旅行史的美国患者分离出的病毒株，显示其可能同时感染了L型和S型新冠病毒。
But one of the U. S. patients with a recent Wuhan travel history isolated a strain of the virus, suggesting it may have been infected with both the L and S-forms.
不过，作者表示目前还无法排除新突变型的可能性。
However, the authors say the possibility of a new mutant cannot be ruled out at present.
本期编辑 周玉华推荐阅读。
This issue editor Zhou Yuhua recommends reading.
